question: Calculate employee turnover rate by department for 2024

join_plan.skeleton_sql:
employees
JOIN departments ON employees.department_id = departments.department_id
JOIN employee_salaries ON employee_salaries.employee_id = employees.employee_id
JOIN positions ON employees.position_id = positions.position_id
JOIN budgets ON budgets.approved_by = employees.employee_id
JOIN sales_territories ON sales_territories.assigned_rep_id = employees.employee_id
JOIN sales_regions ON sales_regions.manager_id = employees.employee_id

sql_generated:
SELECT 
    d.department_id,
    d.name AS department_name,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN e.termination_date IS NOT NULL THEN 1 END) AS terminated_count,
    COUNT(e.employee_id) AS total_count,
    (COUNT(CASE WHEN e.termination_date IS NOT NULL THEN 1 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(e.employee_id)) AS turnover_rate
FROM 
    employees e
JOIN 
    departments d ON e.department_id = d.department_id
WHERE 
    EXTRACT(YEAR FROM e.termination_date) = 2024
GROUP BY 
    d.department_id, d.name;
